    {
      "question": "A company models the profit $P(x)$ (in thousands of rupees) of a product with respect to the production units $x$ (in hundreds) as $P(x) = 2x^3 + x^2 - 5x + 2$. If the cost factor is represented by the divisor $g(x) = 2x - 1$, find the quotient $q(x)$ and verify the division algorithm $P(x) = g(x)q(x) + r(x)$ where $r(x)$ is the remainder.",
      "answer": "$q(x) = x^2 + x - 2$, $r(x) = 0$. Verification: $(2x - 1)(x^2 + x - 2) + 0 = 2x^3 + 2x^2 - 4x - x^2 - x + 2 = 2x^3 + x^2 - 5x + 2$.",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Set up the long division: divide $2x^3 + x^2 - 5x + 2$ by $2x - 1$.",
          "Divide $2x^3$ by $2x$ to get $x^2$. Multiply $x^2(2x-1) = 2x^3 - x^2$. Subtract to get $2x^2 - 5x + 2$.",
          "Divide $2x^2$ by $2x$ to get $x$. Multiply $x(2x-1) = 2x^2 - x$. Subtract to get $-4x + 2$.",
          "Divide $-4x$ by $2x$ to get $-2$. Multiply $-2(2x-1) = -4x + 2$. Subtract to get $0$.",
          "State the quotient $q(x) = x^2 + x - 2$ and remainder $r(x) = 0$.",
          "Multiply $g(x)q(x) + r(x)$ to verify it equals $p(x)$."
        ],
        "derivation": "$2x^3 + x^2 - 5x + 2 = (2x - 1)(x^2) + (2x^2 - 5x + 2) \\\\ 2x^2 - 5x + 2 = (2x - 1)(x) + (-4x + 2) \\\\ -4x + 2 = (2x - 1)(-2) + 0 \\\\ (2x - 1)(x^2 + x - 2) + 0 = 2x^3 + 2x^2 - 4x - x^2 - x + 2 = 2x^3 + x^2 - 5x + 2$"
      },
